This paper is about deep learning for image super-resolution, which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a new architecture for super-resolution networks, which involves iterative up- and down-sampling layers and an error feedback mechanism. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI), as well as multimedia (cs.MM) and neural networks (cs.NE).
